tags.name: UniProtKB
tags.description: The UniProt Knowledgebase (UniProtKB) acts as the global hub of accurate, consistent and expertly curated information on protein sequence and function. Each UniProtKB entry is described by a stable protein identifier (accession ID) and contains core data consisting of the amino acid sequence, protein name or description, taxonomic information and links to relevant scientific publications. Further annotation is added when available, such as protein function, subcellular location and the position of protein features such as active sites, domains and post-translational modifications. Where possible these annotations are described using established biological ontologies, classifications and cross-references. A clear indication of the quality of annotation in the form of evidence attribution of experimental and computational data is added to each piece of data.

get.summary: Get UniProtKB entry by a single accession.
get.description: Search UniProtKB by protein entry accession to return all data associated with that entry. Specify <tt>fields</tt> to return only data for specific sections of that entry that are of interest to you

parameters.name: accession
parameters.description: Unique and stable identifier for each UniProtKB entry

parameters.name: fields
parameters.description: List of entry sections (fields) to be returned, separated by commas. List of valid fields

parameters.name: version
parameters.description: Version of the entry. Versions are integers 1 or above; enter <tt>last</tt> for the latest version.</br>Please note that when passing <tt>version</tt> file formats are restricted to <tt>fasta</tt> and <tt>txt</tt> only

get.summary: Download UniProtKB entries retrieved by a search query. (Max. 10 million entries)
get.description: The stream endpoint uses a request query to return all entries associated with the search term in a single download. Specify <tt>fields</tt> to return only data for specific sections of that entry that are of interest to you The stream endpoint has a maximum limit of 10 million entries. For larger requests, please use the 'UniProtKB asynchronous download job' requests described below. The 'UniProtKB asynchronous download job' requests can be used for any size -- the asynchronous download jobs can be paused and resumed at your convenience, unlike the stream endpoint.

parameters.name: query
parameters.description: Criteria to search UniProtKB. Advanced queries can be built with parentheses and conditionals such as AND, OR and NOT. List of valid search fields

parameters.name: fields
parameters.description: List of entry sections (fields) to be returned, separated by commas. List of valid fields

parameters.name: sort
parameters.description: Specify field by which to sort results. List of valid sort fields

parameters.name: includeIsoform
parameters.description: Specify <tt>true</tt> to include isoforms, default is <tt>false</tt>.

parameters.name: download
parameters.description: Specify <tt>true</tt> to download as file, default is <tt>false</tt>.

get.summary: Retrieve UniProtKB entries by a search query.
get.description: The search endpoint uses a request query to return all entries associated with the search term in a paginated list of entries. Use ‘size’ to specify the number of entries per page of results. Specify <tt>fields</tt> to return only data for specific sections of that entry that are of interest to you

parameters.name: query
parameters.description: Criteria to search UniProtKB. Advanced queries can be built with parentheses and conditionals such as AND, OR and NOT. List of valid search fields

parameters.name: fields
parameters.description: List of entry sections (fields) to be returned, separated by commas. List of valid fields

parameters.name: sort
parameters.description: Specify field by which to sort results. List of valid sort fields

parameters.name: includeIsoform
parameters.description: Specify <tt>true</tt> to include isoforms, default is <tt>false</tt>.

parameters.name: size
parameters.description: Specify the number of entries per page of results (Pagination size). Default is 25, max is 500
